# Commit messages (Conventional Commits)

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>` then optional blank line and body.

- **Subject**: imperative mood, **≤ ~50 chars**, no trailing period.
- **Scope** (optional): area touched (e.g. Tasks, PlantCard, GardenMap).

| Type | Use |
|------|-----|
| `feat` | New feature |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Docs / comments only |
| `style` | Formatting, no behavior change |
| `refactor` | Structure change, same behavior |
| `chore` | Tooling, deps, misc maintenance |

Examples: `feat(Tasks): sync Task_Type with Notion`, `fix(Popover): guard zero-length arrays`, `docs: add commit convention`.
